---
const creds = [
  '10+ years working claims from both sides',
  '7,000+ claims handled',
  'Xactimate and Symbility mastery',
  'Former Licensed Insurance Adjusters on staff',
  'Nationwide coverage',
];

const stats = [
  { value: '7,000+', label: 'Claims Handled' },
  { value: '10+', label: 'Years Experience' },
  { value: '50', label: 'States Covered' },
  { value: '100%', label: 'White Labeled' },
];
---

<section id="about" class="px-5 md:px-8 py-24 max-w-page mx-auto">
  <div class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.1em] uppercase text-accent-teal mb-4">Who We Are</div>
  <h2 class="font-heading text-[2rem] md:text-[2.5rem] font-bold tracking-[-0.02em] text-white mb-4 max-w-[600px]">
    Built by people who've been on both sides of the claim.
  </h2>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1.5fr] gap-10 lg:gap-16 items-start mt-12">

    <aside class="bg-secondary border border-accent/15 rounded-2xl p-8 flex flex-col gap-6">
      <div class="stats-grid">
        {stats.map((s) => (
          <div class="stat-block">
            <div class="stat-value">{s.value}</div>
            <div class="stat-label">{s.label}</div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <div class="border-t border-accent/15 pt-6">
        <ul class="flex flex-col gap-2 list-none p-0 m-0">
          {creds.map((c, i) => (
            <li class={`flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-400 text-[0.875rem] py-2 ${i !== creds.length - 1 ? 'border-b border-accent/15' : ''}`}>
              <span class="text-accent-teal mt-[2px] flex-shrink-0">✓</span>
              {c}
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </aside>

    <div>
      <h3 class="font-heading text-[1.5rem] md:text-[1.75rem] font-bold text-white tracking-[-0.02em] mb-6 leading-[1.3]">
        Our team spent years as licensed insurance adjusters before crossing over to the contractor side.
      </h3>
      <p class="text-slate-400 text-[1.05rem] leading-[1.7] mb-5">
        We've written estimates for carriers, reviewed supplements from the desk, and negotiated claim values from both ends of the phone. That background means we don't guess what adjusters want to see — we know, because we used to be the ones accepting them.
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-400 text-[1.05rem] leading-[1.7] mb-5">
        With over 7,000 claims handled nationwide, Precision gives contractors something they rarely get — a claims management department within their own company that has intimate knowledge of the insurance side of the business.
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-400 text-[1.05rem] leading-[1.7]">
        We work as an extension of your operation. We train, coach, and consult your crew for a smooth handoff. We slot in, we do the work, and you collect what you're owed.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .stats-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .stat-block {
    background: #111e2d;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4px;
  }

  .stat-value {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: #38bdf8;
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: #64748b;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
</style>
